intro: Tenorea heterophylla, commonly known as the variable leaf tenorea, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Myrtaceae, which includes eucalyptus and other aromatic plants. The plant is characterized by its variable leaf shapes, ranging from ovate to linear, depending on environmental conditions. It produces small, white or pink flowers that bloom in spring, attracting various pollinators. The plant is often found in sandy soils and is adapted to arid and semi-arid environments.
